<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-15T18:42:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-15T18:42:00-05:00" n="305" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/504</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Shea</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-15T19:00:00-04:42">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>In reply to your telegram March 14, 6 p.m. Minister for Foreign
                                Affairs assures me that Chile will have nothing to do with peace
                                movement being promoted by the Argentine Republic. Brazilian
                                Minister here also assures me that his country will not join the
                                movement. They do not regard it as serious here. No editorial
                                discussion, news despatches generally from Buenos Aires.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SJH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shea</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>